entries.meaning: A Vietnamese soup with a beef base, typically served with rice noodles and beef or chicken.
examples: PHO is the name of an Annamese soup held in high esteem. It is made with beef, a veal bone, onions, a bayleaf, salt, and pepper, and a small teaspoon of nuoc-man,[sic] a typically Annamese condiment which is used in practically all their dishes.
